WEBVTT

00:08.151 --> 00:09.818
So, last year

00:09.854 --> 00:12.055
the First Lady
handpicked this location

00:12.089 --> 00:15.025
to kick off her Urban
Green Thumb program.

00:15.059 --> 00:17.594
And now she's handpicked you
to investigate a death on the property.

00:17.628 --> 00:20.363
No, no, no. She handpicked
the FBI and then...

00:20.398 --> 00:21.587
they picked me.

00:21.612 --> 00:23.500
So the First Lady
secondhand handpicked you.

00:23.501 --> 00:25.201
Yeah, I guess so.

00:25.236 --> 00:27.704
And I'll tell you what,
I will take that.

00:27.738 --> 00:30.306
Looks like animals
unearthed the remains.

00:30.341 --> 00:31.875
Oh, is that vomit?
Yep.

00:31.909 --> 00:33.043
I'll run a sample through

00:33.077 --> 00:34.878
the LC-MS
back at the lab, but...

00:34.912 --> 00:36.613
Okay, I'm gonna upwind.
You guys can have fun picking

00:36.647 --> 00:38.481
through the vomit.

00:38.516 --> 00:40.150
This looks to be the
pelvis and the femur bone

00:40.184 --> 00:41.918
of a common ground squirrel.

00:41.952 --> 00:45.455
Which means we're most likely
dealing with coyote vomit.

00:45.489 --> 00:47.824
Or a whole pack of them,
judging from the amount.

00:47.858 --> 00:50.960
First instar larvae of the aptly
named <i>Calliphora vomitoria</i>

00:50.995 --> 00:53.063
mean these pieces of person
have been here about two days.

00:53.097 --> 00:58.301
There appears to be
severe trauma to the rib cage.

00:58.335 --> 01:02.472
No teeth marks, so this...
isn't from the coyotes.

01:02.506 --> 01:04.708
I wonder what made them so sick.
Maybe drugs

01:04.742 --> 01:06.543
- in the victim's system?
- Probably the wheat.

01:06.577 --> 01:08.611
Rained a couple of days ago,
and when the grain gets wet,

01:08.646 --> 01:10.780
it releases a toxin
known as vomitoxin.

01:10.815 --> 01:12.082
Which, as the name implies--

01:12.116 --> 01:14.484
We get it, Dr. Hodgins.

01:14.518 --> 01:15.719
Yeah.
Based on the slightly receding

01:15.753 --> 01:18.521
zygomatic, the victim
is Caucasian.

01:18.556 --> 01:21.191
I can't tell much more until we
get the remains back to the lab.

01:21.225 --> 01:22.459
Nobody saw anything.

01:22.493 --> 01:24.461
There was no... security tapes,

01:24.495 --> 01:26.463
no one reported anything-- ah,

01:26.497 --> 01:27.764
I don't think this
is what the First Lady

01:27.798 --> 01:28.865
had in mind, you know,

01:28.899 --> 01:30.433
when she wanted everyone
to garden.

01:30.468 --> 01:32.469
Maybe someone just didn't want
to spring for a funeral.

01:32.503 --> 01:33.670
Wow. Okay. Put these little

01:33.704 --> 01:34.904
things down, continue to
look through your vomit.

01:34.939 --> 01:36.539
Bones, don't
bring those

01:36.574 --> 01:37.841
into the vehicle-- whoa!
Can you just hold this for me?

01:37.875 --> 01:39.676
No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:39.710 --> 01:41.811
You don't want it?
No, no, no, no. I don't want that.

01:48.219 --> 01:50.520
Hey, Angela, They should be back
with the remains

01:50.554 --> 01:52.555
any minute.
Wendell, what happened to you?

01:52.590 --> 01:54.224
Oh, a hockey game. I got checked.
What is it with men

01:54.258 --> 01:56.826
that they're willing
to die for a ball?

01:56.861 --> 01:59.696
It's a puck.
Yeah, I mean, it's still round.

01:59.730 --> 02:01.664
You wear
your injury well, though.

02:01.699 --> 02:04.134
Ah, so you like a rugged,
damaged man.

02:04.168 --> 02:06.770
Well, yeah.
I know I shouldn't, but I do.

02:06.804 --> 02:07.926
Does Brennan know about
your arm?

02:07.951 --> 02:09.239
I'm fine.
'Cause if she didn't

02:09.240 --> 02:10.306
think you were up to speed,
then you could...

02:10.332 --> 02:11.474
I'm fine.

02:11.475 --> 02:12.609
And rugged, remember?

02:12.643 --> 02:14.083
Hey, can I sign your cast?

02:14.111 --> 02:15.578
Yeah.

02:15.613 --> 02:17.413
I can sell it for a lot
when you're famous.

02:19.116 --> 02:20.750
There's blunt force trauma
to the rib cage.

02:20.785 --> 02:23.386
The tibias and fibulas
are fractured.

02:23.420 --> 02:26.623
The grave was shallow and short.
The assailant might've

02:26.657 --> 02:28.624
broken the legs
so the victim would fit.

02:28.649 --> 02:29.772
Probably 
in a hurry.

02:29.773 --> 02:31.594
Yeah, or not strong enough
to dig a grave big enough.

02:31.595 --> 02:34.430
Between the vomit and the body,
we have most of the tissue.

02:34.465 --> 02:36.733
So the coyotes vomited the guy
back onto himself.

02:36.767 --> 02:39.736
We don't know that the victim
was male yet, Mr. Bray.

02:39.770 --> 02:42.672
Are you sure you're up to this?

02:42.706 --> 02:44.040
Aw, it's just
a little boo-boo, right?

02:44.074 --> 02:47.110
Absolutely.
Hey, Angie, nice mermaid.

02:47.144 --> 02:49.813
Uh, the rim around
the auricular surface indicates

02:49.847 --> 02:51.781
an age of late 20s, early 30s.

02:51.816 --> 02:53.983
And the heart-shaped
pelvic inlet suggests gender

02:54.018 --> 02:56.486
so...
I don't think

02:56.520 --> 02:59.289
we need bones to let us know
that the victim was a male.

02:59.323 --> 03:00.456
We have no other way,

03:00.491 --> 03:01.891
Dr. Saroyan.
I think we do.

03:01.926 --> 03:03.526
That mangled piece

03:03.561 --> 03:05.428
of meat is his...?
Yeah.

03:05.462 --> 03:07.831
Breaking my arm seems
like nothing now.

03:11.769 --> 03:12.902
Yeah.

03:12.937 --> 03:14.561
Geez!
Whoa!

03:14.562 --> 03:18.562
